</p><h3 class="likesectionHead"><a id="x1-122000III"></a>Iteration</h3>
<a id="Q1-1-240"></a>
<a id="dx1-122001"></a>
<a id="dx1-122002"></a>
<!--l. 5134--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">splot</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">set </span>and <span class="cmbx-10">unset </span>commands may optionally contain an iteration clause. This has the effect of
executing the basic command multiple times, each time re-evaluating any expressions that make use of the iteration
control variable. Iteration of arbitrary command sequences can be requested using the <span class="cmbx-10">do </span>command. Two forms of
iteration clause are currently supported:
<!--l. 5142--></p><p class="noindent"></p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">for</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="p">intvar</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">=</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">start</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="p">end</span><span class="o">{:</span><span class="p">increment</span><span class="o">}]</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">for</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="p">stringvar</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;in</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"A</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;B</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;C</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;D"</span><span class="o">]</span></span>
<!--l. 5145--></pre>
<!--l. 5148--><p class="noindent">Examples:
<!--l. 5151--></p><p class="noindent"></p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">plot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">for</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="p">filename</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;in</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"A.dat</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;B.dat</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;C.dat"</span><span class="o">]</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">filename</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">2</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;with</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;lines</span></span><span class="p">
