</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">for</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="p">i</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">=</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">]</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">style</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;line</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;i</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;lc</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;rgb</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"blue"</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">unset</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">for</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="p">tag</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">=</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">100</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">200</span><span class="o">]</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">label</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;tag</span></span>
<!--l. 5156--></pre>
<!--l. 5159--><p class="noindent">Nested iteration is supported:
<!--l. 5162--></p><p class="noindent"></p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">for</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="p">i</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">9</span><span class="o">]</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">for</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="p">j</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">9</span><span class="o">]</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">label</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;i</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="p">j</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;sprintf</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="s">"%d"</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="p">i</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="p">j</span><span class="o">)</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">at</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;i</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="p">j</span></span>
<!--l. 5164--></pre>
<!--l. 5167--><p class="noindent">See additional documentation for <span class="cmbx-10">plot iteration (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-178000III"><span class="cmbx-10">117</span><!--tex4ht:ref: plot iteration --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-122003"></a>, <span class="cmbx-10">do (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-103000III"><span class="cmbx-10">78</span><!--tex4ht:ref: do --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-122004"></a>.
<!--l. 5169--></p><p class="noindent">
</p><h3 class="likesectionHead"><a id="x1-123000III"></a>Load</h3>
<a id="Q1-1-242"></a>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<a id="dx1-123001"></a>
<!--l. 5174--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">load </span>command executes each line of the specified input file as if it had been typed in interactively. Files created
by the <span class="cmbx-10">save </span>command can later be <span class="cmbx-10">load</span>ed. Any text file containing valid commands can be created and then
executed by the <span class="cmbx-10">load </span>command. Files being <span class="cmbx-10">load</span>ed may themselves contain <span class="cmbx-10">load </span>or <span class="cmbx-10">call </span>commands. See
<span class="cmbx-10">comments (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-19000I"><span class="cmbx-10">24</span><!--tex4ht:ref: comments --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-123002"></a> for information about comments in commands. To <span class="cmbx-10">load </span>with arguments, see <span class="cmbx-10">call</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-101000III"><span class="cmbx-10">77</span><!--tex4ht:ref: call --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-123003"></a>.
<!--l. 5181--></p><p class="noindent">Syntax: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">load</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"&lt;input-file&gt;"</span></span>
<!--l. 5185--></pre>
<!--l. 5188--><p class="noindent">The name of the input file must be enclosed in quotes.
<!--l. 5190--></p><p class="noindent">The special filename <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>-<span class="cmtt-10">" </span>may be used to <span class="cmbx-10">load </span>commands from standard input. This allows a <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>command file
to accept some commands from standard input. Please see help for <span class="cmbx-10">batch/interactive (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-16000I"><span class="cmbx-10">22</span><!--tex4ht:ref: batch/interactive --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-123004"></a> for more
details.
<!--l. 5194--></p><p class="noindent">On some systems which support a popen function (Unix), the load file can be read from a pipe by starting the file
name with a '<span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>'.
<!--l. 5197--></p><p class="noindent">Examples: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">load</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">'work.gnu'</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">load</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"func.dat"</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">load</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"&lt;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;loadfile_generator.sh"</span></span>
<!--l. 5203--></pre>
<!--l. 5206--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">load </span>command is performed implicitly on any file names given as arguments to <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot</span>. These are loaded in
the order specified, and then <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>exits.
</p><h3 class="likesectionHead"><a id="x1-124000III"></a>Lower</h3>
<a id="Q1-1-244"></a>
<a id="dx1-124001"></a>
<!--l. 5214--><p class="noindent">Syntax: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">lower</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span><span class="p">plot_window_nb</span><span class="o">}</span></span>
<!--l. 5218--></pre>
<!--l. 5221--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">lower </span>command lowers (opposite to <span class="cmbx-10">raise</span>) plot window(s) associated with the interactive terminal of your
gnuplot session, i.e. <span class="cmbx-10">pm</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">win</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">wxt </span>or <span class="cmbx-10">x11</span>. It puts the plot window to bottom in the z-order windows stack of the
window manager of your desktop.
<!--l. 5226--></p><p class="noindent">As <span class="cmbx-10">x11 </span>and <span class="cmbx-10">wxt </span>support multiple plot windows, then by default they lower these windows in descending order of
most recently created on top to the least recently created on bottom. If a plot number is supplied as an optional
parameter, only the associated plot window will be lowered if it exists.
<!--l. 5231--></p><p class="noindent">The optional parameter is ignored for single plot-window terminals, i.e. <span class="cmbx-10">pm </span>and <span class="cmbx-10">win</span>.
</p><h3 class="likesectionHead"><a id="x1-125000III"></a>Pause</h3>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<a id="Q1-1-246"></a>
<a id="dx1-125001"></a>
<!--l. 5239--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">pause </span>command displays any text associated with the command and then waits a specified amount
of time or until the carriage return is pressed. <span class="cmbx-10">pause </span>is especially useful in conjunction with <span class="cmbx-10">load</span>
files.
<!--l. 5243--></p><p class="noindent">Syntax: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">pause</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">&lt;time&gt;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span><span class="s">"&lt;string&gt;"</span><span class="o">}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">pause</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;mouse</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{&lt;</span><span class="p">endcondition</span><span class="o">&gt;}{,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;&lt;</span><span class="p">endcondition</span><span class="o">&gt;}</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;{</span><span class="s">"&lt;string&gt;"</span><span class="o">}</span></span>
<!--l. 5248--></pre>
<!--l. 5251--><p class="noindent"><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>time<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>may be any constant or expression. Choosing -1 will wait until a carriage return is hit, zero (0) won't pause
at all, and a positive number will wait the specified number of seconds. The time is rounded to an integer number of
seconds if subsecond time resolution is not supported by the given platform. <span class="cmbx-10">pause 0 </span>is synonymous with
<span class="cmbx-10">print</span>.
<!--l. 5257--></p><p class="noindent">If the current terminal supports <span class="cmbx-10">mousing</span>, then <span class="cmbx-10">pause mouse </span>will terminate on either a mouse click or
on ctrl-C. For all other terminals, or if mousing is not active, <span class="cmbx-10">pause mouse </span>is equivalent to <span class="cmbx-10">pause</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">-1</span>.
<!--l. 5261--></p><p class="noindent">If one or more end conditions are given after <span class="cmbx-10">pause mouse</span>, then any one of the conditions will terminate the pause.
The possible end conditions are <span class="cmbx-10">keypress</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">button1</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">button2</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">button3</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">close</span>, and <span class="cmbx-10">any</span>. If the pause
terminates on a keypress, then the ascii value of the key pressed is returned in MOUSE_KEY. The
character itself is returned as a one character string in MOUSE_CHAR. Hotkeys (bind command) are
disabled if keypress is one of the end conditions. Zooming is disabled if button3 is one of the end
conditions.
<!--l. 5270--></p><p class="noindent">In all cases the coordinates of the mouse are returned in variables MOUSE_X, MOUSE_Y, MOUSE_X2,
MOUSE_Y2. See <span class="cmbx-10">mouse variables (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-50000I"><span class="cmbx-10">45</span><!--tex4ht:ref: mouse variables --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-125002"></a>.
<!--l. 5273--></p><p class="noindent">Note: Since <span class="cmbx-10">pause </span>communicates with the operating system rather than the graphics, it may behave differently with
different device drivers (depending upon how text and graphics are mixed).
<!--l. 5277--></p><p class="noindent">Examples: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">pause</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">1</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;Wait</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;until</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;a</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;carriage</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;return</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;is</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;hit</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">pause</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">3</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;Wait</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;three</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;seconds</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">pause</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">1</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"Hit</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;return</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;to</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;continue"</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">pause</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">10</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"Isn't</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;this</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;pretty?</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;It's</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;a</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;cubic</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;spline."</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">pause</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;mouse</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"Click</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;any</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;mouse</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;button</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;on</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;selected</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;data</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;point"</span></span><span class="p">
