<!--l. 5882--><p class="noindent">The data points to be plotted are selected according to a loop from <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">start</span><span class="cmbx-10">_point</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>to <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">end</span><span class="cmbx-10">_point</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>with
increment <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">point</span><span class="cmbx-10">_incr</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>and the blocks according to a loop from <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">start</span><span class="cmbx-10">_block</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>to <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">end</span><span class="cmbx-10">_block</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>with
increment <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">block</span><span class="cmbx-10">_incr</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>.
<!--l. 5887--></p><p class="noindent">The first datum in each block is numbered '0', as is the first block in the file.
<!--l. 5890--></p><p class="noindent">Note that records containing unplottable information are counted.
<!--l. 5892--></p><p class="noindent">Any of the numbers can be omitted; the increments default to unity, the start values to the first point or
block, and the end values to the last point or block. If <span class="cmbx-10">every </span>is not specified, all points in all lines are
plotted.
