<!--l. 9524--><p class="noindent">There are some problem cases that arise when numbers like 9.999 are printed with a format that requires both
rounding and a power.
<!--l. 9527--></p><p class="noindent">If the data type for the axis is time/date, the format string must contain valid codes for the 'strftime' function
(outside of <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot</span>, type <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>man strftime<span class="cmtt-10">"</span>). See <span class="cmbx-10">set timefmt (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-313000III"><span class="cmbx-10">211</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set timefmt --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-223002"></a> for a list of the allowed input format
codes.
</p><h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a id="x1-224000III"></a>Time/date specifiers</h5>
<a id="Q1-1-444"></a>
<a id="dx1-224001"></a>
