<!--l. 10422--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set linetype </span>command allows you to redefine the basic linetypes used for plots. The command options are
identical to those for <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>set style line<span class="cmtt-10">"</span>. Unlike line styles, redefinitions by <span class="cmbx-10">set linetype </span>are persistent; they are not
affected by <span class="cmbx-10">reset</span>.
<!--l. 10427--></p><p class="noindent">For example, linetypes one and two default to red and green. If you redefine them like this:
<!--l. 10431--></p><p class="noindent"></p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;linetype</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;lw</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">2</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;lc</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;rgb</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"blue"</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;pointtype</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">6</span></span><span class="p">
