<a id="Q1-1-550"></a>
<!--l. 12115--><p class="noindent">Use <span class="cmbx-10">set palette functions </span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">Rexpr</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">, </span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">Gexpr</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">, </span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">Bexpr</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>to define three formulae for the R(gray), G(gray)
and B(gray) mapping. The three formulae may depend on the variable <span class="cmbx-10">gray </span>which will take values in [0,1] and
should also produce values in [0,1]. Please note that <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>Rexpr<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>might be a formula for the H-value if HSV color space
has been chosen (same for all other formulae and color spaces).
<!--l. 12122--></p><p class="noindent">Examples:
<!--l. 12124--></p><p class="noindent">To produce a full color palette use: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;palette</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;model</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;HSV</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;functions</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;gray</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span></span>
<!--l. 12128--></pre>
