</p><h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a id="x1-294000III"></a>Set style arrow</h5>
<a id="Q1-1-584"></a>
<a id="dx1-294001"></a>
<!--l. 12677--><p class="noindent">Each terminal has a default set of arrow and point types, which can be seen by using the command <span class="cmbx-10">test</span>. <span class="cmbx-10">set style</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">arrow </span>defines a set of arrow types and widths and point types and sizes so that you can refer to them later by an
index instead of repeating all the information at each invocation.
