<!--l. 14263--></p><p class="noindent"><span class="cmbx-10">axis </span>or <span class="cmbx-10">border </span>tells <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>to put the tics (both the tics themselves and the accompanying labels) along the axis
or the border, respectively. If the axis is very close to the border, the <span class="cmbx-10">axis </span>option will move the tic labels to outside
the border. The relevant margin settings will usually be sized badly by the automatic layout algorithm in this
case.
<!--l. 14269--></p><p class="noindent"><span class="cmbx-10">mirror </span>tells <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>to put unlabelled tics at the same positions on the opposite border. <span class="cmbx-10">nomirror </span>does what you
think it does.
<!--l. 14272--></p><p class="noindent"><span class="cmbx-10">in </span>and <span class="cmbx-10">out </span>change the tic marks to be drawn inwards or outwards.
<!--l. 14274--></p><p class="noindent">With <span class="cmbx-10">scale</span>, the size of the tic marks can be adjusted. If <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>minor<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>is not specified, it is 0.5*<span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>major<span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>. The default
size 1.0 for major tics and 0.5 for minor tics is requested by <span class="cmbx-10">scale default</span>.
<!--l. 14278--></p><p class="noindent"><span class="cmbx-10">rotate </span>asks <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>to rotate the text through 90 degrees, which will be done if the terminal driver in use supports
text rotation. <span class="cmbx-10">norotate </span>cancels this. <span class="cmbx-10">rotate by </span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">ang</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>asks for rotation by <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>ang<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>degrees, supported by some
terminal types.
<!--l. 14283--></p><p class="noindent">The defaults are <span class="cmbx-10">border mirror norotate </span>for tics on the x and y axes, and <span class="cmbx-10">border nomirror norotate </span>for tics
on the x2 and y2 axes. For the z axis, the <span class="cmbsy-10">{</span><span class="cmbx-10">axis </span><span class="cmsy-10">| </span><span class="cmbx-10">border</span><span class="cmbsy-10">} </span>option is not available and the default is <span class="cmbx-10">nomirror</span>. If
you do want to mirror the z-axis tics, you might want to create a bit more room for them with <span class="cmbx-10">set</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">border</span>.
<!--l. 14289--></p><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>offset<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>is specified by either x,y or x,y,z, and may be preceded by <span class="cmbx-10">first</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">second</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">graph</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">screen</span>, or
<span class="cmbx-10">character </span>to select the coordinate system. <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>offset<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>is the offset of the tics texts from their default positions, while
the default coordinate system is <span class="cmbx-10">character</span>. See <span class="cmbx-10">coordinates (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-20000I"><span class="cmbx-10">24</span><!--tex4ht:ref: coordinates --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-335003"></a> for details. <span class="cmbx-10">nooffset </span>switches off the
offset.
<!--l. 14295--></p><p class="noindent">Example:
<!--l. 14297--></p><p class="noindent">Move xtics more closely to the plot. </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;offset</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">0</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="p">graph</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">0.05</span></span>
<!--l. 14301--></pre>
<!--l. 14304--><p class="noindent">By default, tic labels are justified automatically depending on the axis and rotation angle to produce aesthetically
pleasing results. If this is not desired, justification can be overridden with an explicit <span class="cmbx-10">left</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">right </span>or <span class="cmbx-10">center </span>keyword.
<span class="cmbx-10">autojustify </span>restores the default behavior.
<!--l. 14309--></p><p class="noindent"><span class="cmbx-10">set xtics </span>with no options restores the default border or axis if xtics are being displayed; otherwise it has no effect.
Any previously specified tic frequency or position <span class="cmsy-10">{</span>and labels<span class="cmsy-10">} </span>are retained.
<!--l. 14313--></p><p class="noindent">Positions of the tics are calculated automatically by default or if the <span class="cmbx-10">autofreq </span>option is given; otherwise they may
be specified in either of two forms:
<!--l. 14317--></p><p class="noindent">The implicit <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>start<span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>, <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>incr<span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>, <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>end<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>form specifies that a series of tics will be plotted on the axis between
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
the values <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>start<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>and <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>end<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>with an increment of <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>incr<span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>. If <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>end<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>is not given, it is assumed
to be infinity. The increment may be negative. If neither <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>start<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>nor <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>end<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>is given, <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>start<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>is
assumed to be negative infinity, <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>end<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>is assumed to be positive infinity, and the tics will be drawn at
integral multiples of <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>incr<span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>. If the axis is logarithmic, the increment will be used as a multiplicative
factor.
<!--l. 14325--></p><p class="noindent">If you specify to a negative <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>start<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>or <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>incr<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>after a numerical value (e.g., <span class="cmbx-10">rotate by </span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">angle</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>or <span class="cmbx-10">offset</span>
<span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">offset</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>), the parser fails because it subtracts <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>start<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>or <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>incr<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>from that value. As a workaround, specify
<span class="cmbx-10">0-</span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">start</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>resp. <span class="cmbx-10">0-</span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">incr</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>in that case.
<!--l. 14330--></p><p class="noindent">Example: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;border</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;offset</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">0</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">0.5</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">5</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">5</span></span>
<!--l. 14334--></pre> <p>Fails with 'invalid expression' at the last comma.</p> <pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;border</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;offset</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">0</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">0.5</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">0</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">5</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">5</span></span>
<!--l. 14340--></pre> <p>or</p> <pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;offset</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">0</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">0.5</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;border</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">5</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">5</span></span>
<!--l. 14346--></pre> Sets tics at the border, tics text with an offset of 0,0.5 characters, and sets the start, increment, and end to -5, 1,
and 5, as requested.
<!--l. 14351--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set grid </span>options 'front', 'back' and 'layerdefault' affect the drawing order of the xtics, too.
<!--l. 14354--></p><p class="noindent">Examples:
<!--l. 14356--></p><p class="noindent">Make tics at 0, 0.5, 1, 1.5, ..., 9.5, 10. </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">0</span><span class="o">,.</span><span class="n">5</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">10</span></span>
<!--l. 14360--></pre>
<!--l. 14363--><p class="noindent">Make tics at ..., -10, -5, 0, 5, 10, ... </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">5</span></span>
<!--l. 14367--></pre>
<!--l. 14370--><p class="noindent">Make tics at 1, 100, 1e4, 1e6, 1e8. </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;logscale</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;x</span><span class="o">;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">100</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">1e8</span></span>
<!--l. 14374--></pre>
<!--l. 14377--><p class="noindent">The explicit (<span class="cmtt-10">"</span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>label<span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">" </span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>pos<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; &lt;</span>level<span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>, ...) form allows arbitrary tic positions or non-numeric tic labels. In this
form, the tics do not need to be listed in numerical order. Each tic has a position, optionally with a label. Note that
the label is a string enclosed by quotes. It may be a constant string, such as <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>hello<span class="cmtt-10">"</span>, may contain formatting
information for converting the position into its label, such as <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>%3f clients<span class="cmtt-10">"</span>, or may be empty, <span class="cmtt-10">""</span>.
See <span class="cmbx-10">set format (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-221000III"><span class="cmbx-10">152</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set format --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-335004"></a> for more information. If no string is given, the default label (numerical) is
used.
<!--l. 14387--></p><p class="noindent">An explicit tic mark has a third parameter, the <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>level<span class="cmtt-10">"</span>. The default is level 0, a major tic. A level of 1 generates a
minor tic. If the level is specified, then the label must also be supplied.
<!--l. 14391--></p><p class="noindent">Examples: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="s">"low"</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">0</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"medium"</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">50</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"high"</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">100</span><span class="o">)</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">2</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">4</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">8</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">16</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">32</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">64</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">128</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">256</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">512</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">1024</span><span class="o">)</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;ytics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="s">"bottom"</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">0</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">""</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"top"</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">20</span><span class="o">)</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;ytics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="s">"bottom"</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">0</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">""</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">10</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"top"</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">20</span><span class="o">)</span></span>
<!--l. 14398--></pre>
<!--l. 14401--><p class="noindent">In the second example, all tics are labelled. In the third, only the end tics are labelled. In the fourth, the unlabeled
tic is a minor tic.
<!--l. 14404--></p><p class="noindent">Normally if explicit tics are given, they are used instead of auto-generated tics. Conversely if you specify
<span class="cmbx-10">set xtics auto </span>or the like it will erase any previously specified explicit tics. You can mix explicit
and auto- generated tics by using the keyword <span class="cmbx-10">add</span>, which must appear before the tic style being
added.
<!--l. 14410--></p><p class="noindent">Example: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">0</span><span class="o">,.</span><span class="n">5</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">10</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;add</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="s">"Pi"</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">3.14159</span><span class="o">)</span></span>
<!--l. 14415--></pre>
<!--l. 14418--><p class="noindent">This will automatically generate tic marks every 0.5 along x, but will also add an explicit labeled tic mark at
pi.
<!--l. 14421--></p><p class="noindent">However they are specified, tics will only be plotted when in range.
<!--l. 14423--></p><p class="noindent">Format (or omission) of the tic labels is controlled by <span class="cmbx-10">set format</span>, unless the explicit text of a label is included in
the <span class="cmbx-10">set xtics (</span><span class="cmtt-10">"</span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">label</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">"</span><span class="cmbx-10">) </span>form.
<!--l. 14426--></p><p class="noindent">Minor (unlabelled) tics can be added automatically by the <span class="cmbx-10">set mxtics </span>command, or at explicit positions by the <span class="cmbx-10">set</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">xtics (</span><span class="cmtt-10">"" </span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">pos</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span><span class="cmbx-10">1, ...) </span>form.
</p><h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a id="x1-336000III"></a>Xtics time_data</h5>
<a id="Q1-1-668"></a>
<!--l. 14433--><p class="noindent">In case of timeseries data, axis tic position values must be given as quoted dates or times according to the format
<span class="cmbx-10">timefmt</span>. If the <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>start<span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>, <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>incr<span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>, <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>end<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>form is used, <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>start<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>and <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>end<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>must be given according to <span class="cmbx-10">timefmt</span>,
but <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>incr<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>must be in seconds. Times will be written out according to the format given on <span class="cmbx-10">set format</span>,
however.
<!--l. 14439--></p><p class="noindent">Examples: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xdata</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;time</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;timefmt</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"%d/%m"</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;format</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"%b</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;%d"</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xrange</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="s">"01/12"</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="s">"06/12"</span><span class="o">]</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"01/12"</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">172800</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"05/12"</span></span><span class="p">

</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xdata</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;time</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;timefmt</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"%d/%m"</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;format</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"%b</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;%d"</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xrange</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="s">"01/12"</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="s">"06/12"</span><span class="o">]</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xtics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="s">"01/12"</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">""</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"03/12"</span><span class="o">,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"05/12"</span><span class="o">)</span></span>
<!--l. 14457--></pre> Both of these will produce tics <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>Dec 1<span class="cmtt-10">"</span>, <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>Dec 3<span class="cmtt-10">"</span>, and <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>Dec 5<span class="cmtt-10">"</span>, but in the second example the tic at <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>Dec 3<span class="cmtt-10">" </span>will be
unlabelled.
<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a id="x1-337000III"></a>Xtics rangelimited</h5>
<a id="Q1-1-670"></a>
<a id="dx1-337001"></a>
<a id="dx1-337002"></a>
<!--l. 14469--><p class="noindent">This option limits both the auto-generated axis tic labels and the corresponding plot border to the range of
values actually present in the data that has been plotted. Note that this is independent of the current
range limits for the plot. For example, suppose that the data in <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>file.dat<span class="cmtt-10">" </span>all lies in the range 2 <span class="cmmi-10">&lt; </span>y
<span class="cmmi-10">&lt; </span>4. Then the following commands will create a plot for which the left-hand plot border (y axis) is
drawn for only this portion of the total y range, and only the axis tics in this region are generated.
I.e., the plot will be scaled to the full range on y, but there will be a gap between 0 and 2 on the left
border and another gap between 4 and 10. This style is sometimes referred to as a <span class="cmbx-10">range-frame </span>graph.
</p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;border</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">3</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;yrange</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="n">0</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">]</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;ytics</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;nomirror</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;rangelimited</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">plot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"file.dat"</span></span>
<!--l. 14485--></pre>
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-338000III"></a>Xyplane</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-672"></a>
<a id="dx1-338001"></a>
<!--l. 14495--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set xyplane </span>command adjusts the position at which the xy plane is drawn in a 3D plot. The synonym <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>set
ticslevel<span class="cmtt-10">" </span>is accepted for backwards compatibility.
<!--l. 14499--></p><p class="noindent">Syntax: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xyplane</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;at</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">&lt;zvalue&gt;</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xyplane</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;relative</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">&lt;frac&gt;</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;ticslevel</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">&lt;frac&gt;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;equivalent</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;to</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;xyplane</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;relative</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">show</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xyplane</span></span>
<!--l. 14506--></pre>
<!--l. 14509--><p class="noindent">The form <span class="cmbx-10">set xyplane relative </span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">frac</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>places the xy plane below the range in Z, where the distance from the xy
plane to Zmin is given as a fraction of the total range in z. The default value is 0.5. Negative values are permitted,
but tic labels on the three axes may overlap. The older, deprecated, form <span class="cmbx-10">set ticslevel </span>is retained for backwards
compatibility.
<!--l. 14515--></p><p class="noindent">To place the xy-plane at a position 'pos' on the z-axis, <span class="cmbx-10">ticslevel </span>may be set equal to (pos - zmin) / (zmin - zmax).
However, this position will change if the z range is changed.
<!--l. 14519--></p><p class="noindent">The alternative form <span class="cmbx-10">set xyplane at </span><span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span><span class="cmbx-10">zvalue</span><span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>fixes the placement of the xy plane at a specific Z value regardless
of the current z range. Thus to force the x, y, and z axes to meet at a common origin one would specify <span class="cmbx-10">set xyplane</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">at 0</span>.
<!--l. 14524--></p><p class="noindent">See also <span class="cmbx-10">set view (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-320000III"><span class="cmbx-10">213</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set view --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-338002"></a>, and <span class="cmbx-10">set zeroaxis (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-360000III"><span class="cmbx-10">228</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set zeroaxis --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-338003"></a>.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-339000III"></a>Xzeroaxis</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-674"></a>
<a id="dx1-339001"></a>
<a id="dx1-339002"></a>
<!--l. 14537--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set xzeroaxis </span>command draws a line at y = 0. For details, please see <span class="cmbx-10">set zeroaxis (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-360000III"><span class="cmbx-10">228</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set zeroaxis --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-339003"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-340000III"></a>Y2data</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-676"></a>
<a id="dx1-340001"></a>
<!--l. 14547--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set y2data </span>command sets y2 (right-hand) axis data to timeseries (dates/times). Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xdata</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-330000III"><span class="cmbx-10">216</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xdata --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-340002"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-341000III"></a>Y2dtics</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-678"></a>
<a id="dx1-341001"></a>
<a id="dx1-341002"></a>
<!--l. 14560--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set y2dtics </span>command changes tics on the y2 (right-hand) axis to days of the week. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xdtics</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-331000III"><span class="cmbx-10">216</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xdtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-341003"></a> for details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-342000III"></a>Y2label</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-680"></a>
<a id="dx1-342001"></a>
<!--l. 14570--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set y2label </span>command sets the label for the y2 (right-hand) axis. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xlabel (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-332000III"><span class="cmbx-10">217</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xlabel --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-342002"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-343000III"></a>Y2mtics</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-682"></a>
<a id="dx1-343001"></a>
<a id="dx1-343002"></a>
<!--l. 14584--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set y2mtics </span>command changes tics on the y2 (right-hand) axis to months of the year. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xmtics</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-333000III"><span class="cmbx-10">218</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xmtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-343003"></a> for details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-344000III"></a>Y2range</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-684"></a>
<a id="dx1-344001"></a>
<!--l. 14594--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set y2range </span>command sets the vertical range that will be displayed on the y2 (right-hand) axis. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">xrange (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-334000III"><span class="cmbx-10">218</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xrange --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-344002"></a> for details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-345000III"></a>Y2tics</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-686"></a>
<a id="dx1-345001"></a>
<a id="dx1-345002"></a>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 14608--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set y2tics </span>command controls major (labelled) tics on the y2 (right-hand) axis. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xtics (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-335000III"><span class="cmbx-10">220</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-345003"></a>
for details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-346000III"></a>Y2zeroaxis</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-688"></a>
<a id="dx1-346001"></a>
<a id="dx1-346002"></a>
<!--l. 14622--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set y2zeroaxis </span>command draws a line at the origin of the y2 (right-hand) axis (x2 = 0). For details, please see
<span class="cmbx-10">set zeroaxis (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-360000III"><span class="cmbx-10">228</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set zeroaxis --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-346003"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-347000III"></a>Ydata</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-690"></a>
<a id="dx1-347001"></a>
<!--l. 14632--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set ydata </span>commands sets y-axis data to timeseries (dates/times). Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xdata (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-330000III"><span class="cmbx-10">216</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xdata --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-347002"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-348000III"></a>Ydtics</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-692"></a>
<a id="dx1-348001"></a>
<a id="dx1-348002"></a>
<!--l. 14646--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set ydtics </span>command changes tics on the y axis to days of the week. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xdtics (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-331000III"><span class="cmbx-10">216</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xdtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-348003"></a> for
details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-349000III"></a>Ylabel</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-694"></a>
<a id="dx1-349001"></a>
<!--l. 14656--><p class="noindent">This command sets the label for the y axis. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xlabel (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-332000III"><span class="cmbx-10">217</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xlabel --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-349002"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-350000III"></a>Ymtics</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-696"></a>
<a id="dx1-350001"></a>
<a id="dx1-350002"></a>
<!--l. 14669--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set ymtics </span>command changes tics on the y axis to months of the year. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xmtics (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-333000III"><span class="cmbx-10">218</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xmtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-350003"></a> for
details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-351000III"></a>Yrange</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-698"></a>
<a id="dx1-351001"></a>
<!--l. 14679--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set yrange </span>command sets the vertical range that will be displayed on the y axis. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xrange</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-334000III"><span class="cmbx-10">218</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xrange --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-351002"></a> for details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-352000III"></a>Ytics</h4>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<a id="Q1-1-700"></a>
<a id="dx1-352001"></a>
<a id="dx1-352002"></a>
<!--l. 14693--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set ytics </span>command controls major (labelled) tics on the y axis. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xtics (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-335000III"><span class="cmbx-10">220</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-352003"></a> for
details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-353000III"></a>Yzeroaxis</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-702"></a>
<a id="dx1-353001"></a>
<a id="dx1-353002"></a>
<!--l. 14707--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set yzeroaxis </span>command draws a line at x = 0. For details, please see <span class="cmbx-10">set zeroaxis (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-360000III"><span class="cmbx-10">228</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set zeroaxis --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-353003"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-354000III"></a>Zdata</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-704"></a>
<a id="dx1-354001"></a>
<!--l. 14717--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set zdata </span>command sets zaxis data to timeseries (dates/times). Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xdata (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-330000III"><span class="cmbx-10">216</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xdata --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-354002"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-355000III"></a>Zdtics</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-706"></a>
<a id="dx1-355001"></a>
<a id="dx1-355002"></a>
<!--l. 14731--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set zdtics </span>command changes tics on the z axis to days of the week. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xdtics (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-331000III"><span class="cmbx-10">216</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xdtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-355003"></a> for
details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-356000III"></a>Zzeroaxis</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-708"></a>
<a id="dx1-356001"></a>
<a id="dx1-356002"></a>
<!--l. 14745--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set zzeroaxis </span>command draws a line through (x=0,y=0). This has no effect on 2D plots, including splot with
<span class="cmbx-10">set view map</span>. For details, please see <span class="cmbx-10">set zeroaxis (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-360000III"><span class="cmbx-10">228</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set zeroaxis --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-356003"></a> and <span class="cmbx-10">set xyplane (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-338000III"><span class="cmbx-10">224</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xyplane --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-356004"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-357000III"></a>Cbdata</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-710"></a>
<a id="dx1-357001"></a>
<!--l. 14756--><p class="noindent">Set color box axis data to timeseries (dates/times). Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xdata (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-330000III"><span class="cmbx-10">216</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xdata --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-357002"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-358000III"></a>Cbdtics</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-712"></a>
<a id="dx1-358001"></a>
<a id="dx1-358002"></a>
<!--l. 14769--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set cbdtics </span>command changes tics on the color box axis to days of the week. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xdtics (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-331000III"><span class="cmbx-10">216</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xdtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-358003"></a>
for details.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-359000III"></a>Zero</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-714"></a>
<a id="dx1-359001"></a>
<!--l. 14779--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">zero </span>value is the default threshold for values approaching 0.0.
<!--l. 14781--></p><p class="noindent">Syntax: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;zero</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">&lt;expression&gt;</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">show</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;zero</span></span>
<!--l. 14786--></pre>
<!--l. 14789--><p class="noindent"><span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>will not plot a point if its imaginary part is greater in magnitude than the <span class="cmbx-10">zero </span>threshold.
This threshold is also used in various other parts of <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>as a (crude) numerical-error threshold.
The default <span class="cmbx-10">zero </span>value is 1e-8. <span class="cmbx-10">zero </span>values larger than 1e-3 (the reciprocal of the number of pixels
in a typical bitmap display) should probably be avoided, but it is not unreasonable to set <span class="cmbx-10">zero </span>to
0.0.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-360000III"></a>Zeroaxis</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-716"></a>
<a id="dx1-360001"></a>
<!--l. 14805--><p class="noindent">The x axis may be drawn by <span class="cmbx-10">set xzeroaxis </span>and removed by <span class="cmbx-10">unset xzeroaxis</span>. Similar commands behave similarly
for the y, x2, y2, and z axes.
<!--l. 14808--></p><p class="noindent">Syntax: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span><span class="p">x</span><span class="o">|</span><span class="p">x2</span><span class="o">|</span><span class="p">y</span><span class="o">|</span><span class="p">y2</span><span class="o">|</span><span class="p">z</span><span class="o">}</span><span class="p">zeroaxis</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;{</span><span class="p">linestyle</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">|</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">ls</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">&lt;line_style&gt;</span><span class="o">}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">|</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;{</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">linetype</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">|</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">lt</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">&lt;line_type&gt;</span><span class="o">}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">linewidth</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">|</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">lw</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">&lt;line_width&gt;</span><span class="o">}}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">unset</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span><span class="p">x</span><span class="o">|</span><span class="p">x2</span><span class="o">|</span><span class="p">y</span><span class="o">|</span><span class="p">y2</span><span class="o">|</span><span class="p">z</span><span class="o">}</span><span class="p">zeroaxis</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">show</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span><span class="p">x</span><span class="o">|</span><span class="p">y</span><span class="o">|</span><span class="p">z</span><span class="o">}</span><span class="p">zeroaxis</span></span>
<!--l. 14816--></pre>
<!--l. 14820--><p class="noindent">By default, these options are off. The selected zero axis is drawn with a line of type <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>line_type<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>and
width <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>line_width<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>(if supported by the terminal driver currently in use), or a user-defined style
<span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>line_style<span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>.
<!--l. 14825--></p><p class="noindent">If no linetype is specified, any zero axes selected will be drawn using the axis linetype (linetype 0).
<!--l. 14828--></p><p class="noindent"><span class="cmbx-10">set zeroaxis </span>is equivalent to <span class="cmbx-10">set xzeroaxis; set yzeroaxis</span>. Note that the z-axis must be set separately using <span class="cmbx-10">set</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">zzeroaxis</span>.
<!--l. 14831--></p><p class="noindent">Examples:
<!--l. 14833--></p><p class="noindent">To simply have the y=0 axis drawn visibly:
<!--l. 14836--></p><p class="noindent"></p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xzeroaxis</span></span>
<!--l. 14838--></pre>
<!--l. 14841--><p class="noindent">If you want a thick line in a different color or pattern, instead:
<!--l. 14844--></p><p class="noindent"></p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xzeroaxis</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;linetype</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">3</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;linewidth</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">2.5</span></span>
<!--l. 14846--></pre>
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-361000III"></a>Zlabel</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-718"></a>
<a id="dx1-361001"></a>
<!--l. 14856--><p class="noindent">This command sets the label for the z axis. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xlabel (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-332000III"><span class="cmbx-10">217</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xlabel --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-361002"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-362000III"></a>Zmtics</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-720"></a>
<a id="dx1-362001"></a>
<a id="dx1-362002"></a>
<!--l. 14869--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set zmtics </span>command changes tics on the z axis to months of the year. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xmtics (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-333000III"><span class="cmbx-10">218</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xmtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-362003"></a> for
details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-363000III"></a>Zrange</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-722"></a>
<a id="dx1-363001"></a>
<!--l. 14879--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set zrange </span>command sets the range that will be displayed on the z axis. The zrange is used only by <span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>and
is ignored by <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xrange (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-334000III"><span class="cmbx-10">218</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xrange --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-363002"></a> for details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-364000III"></a>Ztics</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-724"></a>
<a id="dx1-364001"></a>
<a id="dx1-364002"></a>
<!--l. 14894--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set ztics </span>command controls major (labelled) tics on the z axis. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xtics (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-335000III"><span class="cmbx-10">220</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-364003"></a> for
details.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-365000III"></a>Cblabel</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-726"></a>
<a id="dx1-365001"></a>
<!--l. 14904--><p class="noindent">This command sets the label for the color box axis. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xlabel (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-332000III"><span class="cmbx-10">217</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xlabel --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-365002"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-366000III"></a>Cbmtics</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-728"></a>
<a id="dx1-366001"></a>
<a id="dx1-366002"></a>
<!--l. 14917--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set cbmtics </span>command changes tics on the color box axis to months of the year. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xmtics</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-333000III"><span class="cmbx-10">218</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xmtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-366003"></a> for details.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-367000III"></a>Cbrange</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-730"></a>
<a id="dx1-367001"></a>
<!--l. 14927--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set cbrange </span>command sets the range of values which are colored using the current <span class="cmbx-10">palette </span>by styles <span class="cmbx-10">with</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">pm3d</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">with image </span>and <span class="cmbx-10">with palette</span>. Values outside of the color range use color of the nearest
extreme.
<!--l. 14931--></p><p class="noindent">If the cb-axis is autoscaled in <span class="cmbx-10">splot</span>, then the colorbox range is taken from <span class="cmbx-10">zrange</span>. Points drawn in <span class="cmbx-10">splot ...</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">pm3d</span><span class="cmsy-10">|</span><span class="cmbx-10">palette </span>can be filtered by using different <span class="cmbx-10">zrange </span>and <span class="cmbx-10">cbrange</span>.
<!--l. 14935--></p><p class="noindent">Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xrange (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-334000III"><span class="cmbx-10">218</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xrange --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-367002"></a> for details on <span class="cmbx-10">set cbrange (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-367000III"><span class="cmbx-10">230</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set cbrange --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-367003"></a> syntax. See also <span class="cmbx-10">set palette (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-274000III"><span class="cmbx-10">187</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set palette --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-367004"></a> and
<span class="cmbx-10">set colorbox (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-204000III"><span class="cmbx-10">140</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set colorbox --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-367005"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-368000III"></a>Cbtics</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-732"></a>
<a id="dx1-368001"></a>
<a id="dx1-368002"></a>
<!--l. 14949--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">set cbtics </span>command controls major (labelled) tics on the color box axis. Please see <span class="cmbx-10">set xtics (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-335000III"><span class="cmbx-10">220</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xtics --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-368003"></a> for
details.
</p><h3 class="likesectionHead"><a id="x1-369000III"></a>Shell</h3>
<a id="Q1-1-734"></a>
<a id="dx1-369001"></a>
<!--l. 14956--><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">shell </span>command spawns an interactive shell. To return to <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot</span>, type <span class="cmbx-10">logout </span>if using VMS, <span class="cmbx-10">exit </span>or the
END-OF-FILE character if using Unix, or <span class="cmbx-10">exit </span>if using MS-DOS or OS/2.
<!--l. 14960--></p><p class="noindent">There are two ways of spawning a shell command: using <span class="cmbx-10">system </span>command or via <span class="cmbx-10">! </span>($ if using VMS).
The former command takes a string as a parameter and thus it can be used anywhere among other
gnuplot commands, while the latter syntax requires to be the only command on the line. Control
will return immediately to <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>after this command is executed. For example, in MS-DOS or
OS/2,
<!--l. 14968--></p><p class="noindent"></p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">!</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">dir</span></span>
<!--l. 14970--></pre> <p>or</p> <pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">system</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"dir"</span></span>
<!--l. 14976--></pre>
<!--l. 14979--><p class="noindent">prints a directory listing and then returns to <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot</span>.
<!--l. 14981--></p><p class="noindent">Other examples of the former syntax: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">system</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"date"</span><span class="o">;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;time</span><span class="o">;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">plot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"a.dat"</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">print</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">if</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="k">print</span><span class="o">)</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">replot</span><span class="o">;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;out</span><span class="o">;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">system</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"lpr</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="s">&nbsp;x.ps"</span></span>
<!--l. 14986--></pre>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<h3 class="likesectionHead"><a id="x1-370000III"></a>Splot</h3>
<a id="Q1-1-736"></a>
<a id="dx1-370001"></a>
<!--l. 14993--><p class="noindent"><span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>is the command for drawing 3D plots (well, actually projections on a 2D surface, but you knew that). It can
create a plot from functions or data read from files in a manner very similar to the <span class="cmbx-10">plot </span>command. <span class="cmbx-10">splot</span>
provides only a single x, y, and z axis; there is no equivalent to the x2 and y2 secondary axes provided by
<span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>.
<!--l. 14999--></p><p class="noindent">See the <span class="cmbx-10">plot (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-126000III"><span class="cmbx-10">93</span><!--tex4ht:ref: plot --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-370002"></a> command for many options available in both 2D and 3D plots.
<!--l. 15001--></p><p class="noindent">Syntax: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">splot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{&lt;</span><span class="p">ranges</span><span class="o">&gt;}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{&lt;</span><span class="p">iteration</span><span class="o">&gt;}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">&lt;function&gt;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">|</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">"&lt;datafile&gt;"</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span><span class="p">datafile</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="p">modifiers</span><span class="o">}}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{&lt;</span><span class="p">title</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="p">spec</span><span class="o">&gt;}</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;{</span><span class="p">with</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">&lt;style&gt;</span><span class="o">}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{,</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;{</span><span class="p">definitions</span><span class="o">{,}}</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;&lt;</span><span class="p">function</span><span class="o">&gt;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;...}</span></span>
<!--l. 15009--></pre>
<!--l. 15012--><p class="noindent">where either a <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>function<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>or the name of a data file enclosed in quotes is supplied. The function can be a
mathematical expression, or a triple of mathematical expressions in parametric mode.
<!--l. 15016--></p><p class="noindent">By default <span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>draws the xy plane completely below the plotted data. The offset between the lowest ztic and the
xy plane can be changed by <span class="cmbx-10">set xyplane</span>. The orientation of a <span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>projection is controlled by <span class="cmbx-10">set view</span>. See <span class="cmbx-10">set</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">view (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-320000III"><span class="cmbx-10">213</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set view --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-370003"></a> and <span class="cmbx-10">set xyplane (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-338000III"><span class="cmbx-10">224</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xyplane --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-370004"></a> for more information.
<!--l. 15021--></p><p class="noindent">The syntax for setting ranges on the <span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>command is the same as for <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>. In non-parametric mode, the order in
which ranges must be given is <span class="cmbx-10">xrange</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">yrange</span>, and <span class="cmbx-10">zrange</span>. In parametric mode, the order is <span class="cmbx-10">urange</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">vrange</span>,
<span class="cmbx-10">xrange</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">yrange</span>, and <span class="cmbx-10">zrange</span>.
<!--l. 15026--></p><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">title </span>option is the same as in <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>. The operation of <span class="cmbx-10">with </span>is also the same as in <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>, except that the plotting
styles available to <span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>are limited to <span class="cmbx-10">lines</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">points</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">linespoints</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">dots</span>, and <span class="cmbx-10">impulses</span>; the error-bar capabilities of
<span class="cmbx-10">plot </span>are not available for <span class="cmbx-10">splot</span>.
<!--l. 15031--></p><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">datafile </span>options have more differences.
<!--l. 15033--></p><p class="noindent">See also <span class="cmbx-10">show plot (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-264000III"><span class="cmbx-10">182</span><!--tex4ht:ref: show plot --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-370005"></a>.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-371000III"></a>Data-file</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-738"></a>
<!--l. 15038--><p class="noindent"><span class="cmbx-10">Splot</span>, like <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>, can display from a file.
<!--l. 15040--></p><p class="noindent">Syntax: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">splot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">'&lt;file_name&gt;'</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span><span class="p">binary</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="p">binary</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;list</span><span class="o">&gt;}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{{</span><span class="p">nonuniform</span><span class="o">}</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">matrix</span><span class="o">}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span><span class="p">index</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="p">index</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;list</span><span class="o">&gt;}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span><span class="p">every</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="p">every</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;list</span><span class="o">&gt;}</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span><span class="p">using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="p">using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;list</span><span class="o">&gt;}</span></span>
<!--l. 15048--></pre>
<!--l. 15051--><p class="noindent">The special filenames <span class="cmtt-10">"" </span>and <span class="cmtt-10">"</span><span class="cmbx-10">-</span><span class="cmtt-10">" </span>are permitted, as in <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>. See <span class="cmbx-10">special-filenames (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-162000III"><span class="cmbx-10">106</span><!--tex4ht:ref: special-filenames --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-371001"></a>.
<!--l. 15054--></p><p class="noindent">In brief, <span class="cmbx-10">binary </span>and <span class="cmbx-10">matrix </span>indicate that the data are in a special form, <span class="cmbx-10">index </span>selects which data sets
in a multi-data-set file are to be plotted, <span class="cmbx-10">every </span>specifies which datalines (subsets) within a single
data set are to be plotted, and <span class="cmbx-10">using </span>determines how the columns within a single record are to be
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
interpreted.
<!--l. 15060--></p><p class="noindent">The options <span class="cmbx-10">index </span>and <span class="cmbx-10">every </span>behave the same way as with <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>; <span class="cmbx-10">using </span>does so also, except that the <span class="cmbx-10">using </span>list
must provide three entries instead of two.
<!--l. 15064--></p><p class="noindent">The <span class="cmbx-10">plot </span>options <span class="cmbx-10">thru </span>and <span class="cmbx-10">smooth </span>are not available for <span class="cmbx-10">splot</span>, but <span class="cmbx-10">cntrparam </span>and <span class="cmbx-10">dgrid3d </span>provide limited
smoothing capabilities.
<!--l. 15067--></p><p class="noindent">Data file organization is essentially the same as for <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>, except that each point is an (x,y,z) triple. If only a single
value is provided, it will be used for z, the datablock number will be used for y, and the index of the data point in
the datablock will be used for x. If two or four values are provided, <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>uses the last value for calculating the
color in pm3d plots. Three values are interpreted as an (x,y,z) triple. Additional values are generally used as errors,
which can be used by <span class="cmbx-10">fit</span>.
<!--l. 15075--></p><p class="noindent">Single blank records separate datablocks in a <span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>datafile; <span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>treats datablocks as the equivalent of function
y-isolines. No line will join points separated by a blank record. If all datablocks contain the same number of points,
<span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>will draw cross-isolines between datablocks, connecting corresponding points. This is termed <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>grid data<span class="cmtt-10">"</span>,
and is required for drawing a surface, for contouring (<span class="cmbx-10">set contour</span>) and hidden-line removal (<span class="cmbx-10">set hidden3d</span>). See
also <span class="cmbx-10">splot grid</span><span class="cmbx-10">_data (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-374000III"><span class="cmbx-10">235</span><!--tex4ht:ref: splot grid_data --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-371002"></a>.
<!--l. 15083--></p><p class="noindent">It is no longer necessary to specify <span class="cmbx-10">parametric </span>mode for three-column <span class="cmbx-10">splot</span>s.
</p><h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a id="x1-372000III"></a>Matrix</h5>
<a id="Q1-1-740"></a>
<!--l. 15097--><p class="noindent">Gnuplot can interpret matrix input in two different ways. The first of these assumes a uniform grid of x and y
coordinates, and assigns each value in the input matrix to one element of this uniform grid. This is the default
for ascii data input, but not for binary input. Example commands for plotting uniform matrix data:
</p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">splot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">'file'</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;matrix</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">2</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">3</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;ascii</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;input</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">splot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">'file'</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;binary</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;general</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">2</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">3</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;binary</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;input</span></span>
<!--l. 15106--></pre>
<!--l. 15109--><p class="noindent">In a uniform grid matrix the z-values are read in a row at a time, i. e., </p><pre><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z11</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z12</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z13</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z14</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;...</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z21</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z22</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z23</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z24</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;...</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z31</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z32</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z33</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;z34</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;...</span>
<!--l. 15115--></pre> and so forth.
<!--l. 15119--><p class="noindent">For ascii input, a blank line or comment line ends the matrix, and starts a new surface mesh. You can select among
the meshes inside a file by the <span class="cmbx-10">index </span>option to the <span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>command, as usual. <a id="dx1-372001"></a>The second interpretation assumes a
non-uniform grid with explicit x and y coordinates. The first row of input data contains the y coordinates; the first
column of input data contains the x coordinates. For binary input data, the first element of the first row must
contain the number of data columns. (This number is ignored for ascii input). Both the coordinates and the data
values in a binary input are treated as single precision floats. Example commands for plotting non-uniform matrix
data: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">splot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">'file'</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;nonuniform</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;matrix</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">2</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">3</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;ascii</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;input</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">splot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">'file'</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;binary</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;matrix</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">2</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">3</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;binary</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;input</span></span>
<!--l. 15134--></pre>
<!--l. 15137--><p class="noindent">Thus the data organization for non-uniform matrix input is
<!--l. 15140--></p><p class="noindent"></p><pre><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;N+1&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;y0&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;y1&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;y2&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;...</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;yN&gt;</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;x0&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z0,0&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z0,1&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z0,2&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;...</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z0,N&gt;</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;x1&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z1,0&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z1,1&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z1,2&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;...</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z1,N&gt;</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;:</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;:</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;:</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;:</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;...</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;:</span>
<!--l. 15145--></pre>
<!--l. 15148--><p class="noindent">which is then converted into triplets: </p><pre><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;x0&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;y0&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z0,0&gt;</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;x0&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;y1&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z0,1&gt;</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;x0&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;y2&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z0,2&gt;</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;:</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;:</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;:</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;x0&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;yN&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z0,N&gt;</span>

<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;x1&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;y0&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z1,0&gt;</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;x1&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;y1&gt;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;&lt;z1,1&gt;</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;:</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;:</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;:</span>
<!--l. 15164--></pre>
<!--l. 15167--><p class="noindent">These triplets are then converted into <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>iso-curves and then <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>proceeds in the usual manner to do the
rest of the plotting.
<!--l. 15170--></p><p class="noindent">A collection of matrix and vector manipulation routines (in C) is provided in <span class="cmbx-10">binary.c</span>. The routine to write binary
data is
<!--l. 15174--></p><p class="noindent"></p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;int</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;fwrite_matrix</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="p">file</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="p">m</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="p">nrl</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="p">nrl</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="p">ncl</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="p">nch</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="p">row_title</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="p">column_title</span><span class="o">)</span></span>
<!--l. 15176--></pre>
<!--l. 15179--><p class="noindent">An example of using these routines is provided in the file <span class="cmbx-10">bf</span><span class="cmbx-10">_test.c</span>, which generates binary files for the demo file
<span class="cmbx-10">demo/binary.dem</span>.
<!--l. 15182--></p><p class="noindent">Usage in <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">plot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">‘</span><span class="p">a</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="p">dat</span><span class="o">‘</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">matrix</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">plot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">‘</span><span class="p">a</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="p">dat</span><span class="o">‘</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">matrix</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">3</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">plot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">'a.gpbin'</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{</span><span class="p">matrix</span><span class="o">}</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">binary</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">3</span></span>
<!--l. 15188--></pre> will plot rows of the matrix, while using 2:3 will plot matrix columns, and using 1:2 the point coordinates (rather
useless). Applying the <span class="cmbx-10">every </span>option you can specify explicit rows and columns.
<!--l. 15194--><p class="noindent">Example – rescale axes of a matrix in an ascii file: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">splot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">‘</span><span class="p">a</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="p">dat</span><span class="o">‘</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="p">matrix</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="p">$1</span><span class="o">):(</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="p">$2</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">):</span><span class="n">3</span></span>
<!--l. 15198--></pre>
<!--l. 15201--><p class="noindent">Example – plot the 3rd row of a matrix in an ascii file: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">plot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">'a.dat'</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;matrix</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">3</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;every</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">999</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="n">2</span></span>
<!--l. 15205--></pre> (rows are enumerated from 0, thus 2 instead of 3).
<!--l. 15209--><p class="noindent">Gnuplot can read matrix binary files by use of the option <span class="cmbx-10">binary </span>appearing without keyword qualifications unique
to general binary, i.e., <span class="cmbx-10">array</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">record</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">format</span>, or <span class="cmbx-10">filetype</span>. Other general binary keywords for translation should
also apply to matrix binary. (See <span class="cmbx-10">binary general (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-129000III"><span class="cmbx-10">94</span><!--tex4ht:ref: binary general --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-372002"></a> for more details.)
</p><h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a id="x1-373000III"></a>Example datafile</h5>
<a id="Q1-1-742"></a>
<!--l. 15219--><p class="noindent">A simple example of plotting a 3D data file is
<!--l. 15222--></p><p class="noindent"></p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">splot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">'datafile.dat'</span></span>
<!--l. 15224--></pre>
<!--l. 15227--><p class="noindent">where the file <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>datafile.dat<span class="cmtt-10">" </span>might contain:
<!--l. 15230--></p><p class="noindent"></p><pre><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;#</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;The</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;valley</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;of</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;the</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;Gnu.</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;0</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;0</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;10</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;0</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;1</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;10</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;0</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;2</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;10</span>

<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;1</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;0</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;10</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;1</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;1</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;5</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;1</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;2</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;10</span>

<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;2</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;0</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;10</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;2</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;1</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;1</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;2</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;2</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;10</span>

<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;3</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;0</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;10</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;3</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;1</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;0</span>
<span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;3</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;2</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;10</span>
<!--l. 15259--></pre>
<!--l. 15262--><p class="noindent">Note that <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>datafile.dat<span class="cmtt-10">" </span>defines a 4 by 3 grid ( 4 rows of 3 points each ). Rows (datablocks) are separated by blank
records.
<!--l. 15265--></p><p class="noindent">Note also that the x value is held constant within each dataline. If you instead keep y constant, and plot with
hidden-line removal enabled, you will find that the surface is drawn 'inside-out'.
<!--l. 15269--></p><p class="noindent">Actually for grid data it is not necessary to keep the x values constant within a datablock, nor is it necessary to keep
the same sequence of y values. <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>requires only that the number of points be the same for each datablock.
However since the surface mesh, from which contours are derived, connects sequentially corresponding points, the
effect of an irregular grid on a surface plot is unpredictable and should be examined on a case-by-case
basis.
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-374000III"></a>Grid data</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-744"></a>
<a id="dx1-374001"></a>
<!--l. 15282--><p class="noindent">The 3D routines are designed for points in a grid format, with one sample, datapoint, at each mesh intersection; the
datapoints may originate from either evaluating a function, see <span class="cmbx-10">set isosamples (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-230000III"><span class="cmbx-10">158</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set isosamples --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-374002"></a>, or reading a datafile, see
<span class="cmbx-10">splot datafile (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-371000III"><span class="cmbx-10">231</span><!--tex4ht:ref: splot datafile --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-374003"></a>. The term <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>isoline<span class="cmtt-10">" </span>is applied to the mesh lines for both functions and data. Note that the
mesh need not be rectangular in x and y, as it may be parameterized in u and v, see <span class="cmbx-10">set isosamples</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-230000III"><span class="cmbx-10">158</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set isosamples --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-374004"></a>.
<!--l. 15289--></p><p class="noindent">However, <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>does not require that format. In the case of functions, 'samples' need not be equal to
'isosamples', i.e., not every x-isoline sample need intersect a y-isoline. In the case of data files, if there are an
equal number of scattered data points in each datablock, then <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>isolines<span class="cmtt-10">" </span>will connect the points in a
datablock, and <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>cross-isolines<span class="cmtt-10">" </span>will connect the corresponding points in each datablock to generate
a <span class="cmtt-10">"</span>surface<span class="cmtt-10">"</span>. In either case, contour and hidden3d modes may give different plots than if the points
were in the intended format. Scattered data can be converted to a <span class="cmsy-10">{</span>different<span class="cmsy-10">} </span>grid format with <span class="cmbx-10">set</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">dgrid3d</span>.
<!--l. 15299--></p><p class="noindent">The contour code tests for z intensity along a line between a point on a y-isoline and the corresponding point in the
next y-isoline. Thus a <span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>contour of a surface with samples on the x-isolines that do not coincide with a y-isoline
intersection will ignore such samples. Try: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;xrange</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[-</span><span class="p">pi</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">2</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="p">pi</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">2</span><span class="o">];</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;yrange</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[-</span><span class="p">pi</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">2</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="p">pi</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">2</span><span class="o">]</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;style</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;function</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;lp</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;contour</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;isosamples</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;samples</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">;</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">splot</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;cos</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="p">x</span><span class="o">)*</span><span class="p">cos</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="p">y</span><span class="o">)</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;samples</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">4</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">replot</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;samples</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="n">10</span><span class="o">,</span><span class="n">4</span><span class="o">;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">replot</span></span>
<!--l. 15312--></pre>
<!--l. 15315--><p class="noindent">
</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-375000III"></a>Splot surfaces</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-746"></a>
<!--l. 15319--><p class="noindent"><span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>can display a surface as a collection of points, or by connecting those points. As with <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>, the points may be
read from a data file or result from evaluation of a function at specified intervals, see <span class="cmbx-10">set isosamples (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-230000III"><span class="cmbx-10">158</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set isosamples --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-375001"></a>.
The surface may be approximated by connecting the points with straight line segments, see <span class="cmbx-10">set surface (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-305000III"><span class="cmbx-10">207</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set surface --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-375002"></a>,
in which case the surface can be made opaque with <span class="cmbx-10">set hidden3d. </span>The orientation from which the 3d surface is
viewed can be changed with <span class="cmbx-10">set view</span>.
<!--l. 15327--></p><p class="noindent">Additionally, for points in a grid format, <span class="cmbx-10">splot </span>can interpolate points having a common amplitude (see <span class="cmbx-10">set</span>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<span class="cmbx-10">contour (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-206000III"><span class="cmbx-10">141</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set contour --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-375003"></a>) and can then connect those new points to display contour lines, either directly
with straight-line segments or smoothed lines (see <span class="cmbx-10">set cntrparam (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-203000III"><span class="cmbx-10">138</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set cntrparam --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-375004"></a>). Functions are already
evaluated in a grid format, determined by <span class="cmbx-10">set isosamples </span>and <span class="cmbx-10">set samples</span>, while file data must
either be in a grid format, as described in <span class="cmbx-10">data-file</span>, or be used to generate a grid (see <span class="cmbx-10">set dgrid3d</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-216000III"><span class="cmbx-10">147</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set dgrid3d --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-375005"></a>).
<!--l. 15335--></p><p class="noindent">Contour lines may be displayed either on the surface or projected onto the base. The base projections of the contour
lines may be written to a file, and then read with <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>, to take advantage of <span class="cmbx-10">plot</span>'s additional formatting
capabilities.
</p><h3 class="likesectionHead"><a id="x1-376000III"></a>Stats (Statistical Summary)</h3>
<a id="Q1-1-748"></a>
<a id="dx1-376001"></a>
<a id="dx1-376002"></a>
<!--l. 15346--><p class="noindent">Syntax: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">stats</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">'filename'</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="p">using</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;N</span><span class="o">[:</span><span class="p">M</span><span class="o">]]</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;[</span><span class="p">name</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">'prefix'</span><span class="o">]</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;[[</span><span class="p">no</span><span class="o">]</span><span class="p">output</span><span class="o">]]</span></span>
<!--l. 15350--></pre> This command prepares a statistical summary of the data in one or two columns of a file. The using specifier is
interpreted in the same way as for plot commands. See <span class="cmbx-10">plot (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-126000III"><span class="cmbx-10">93</span><!--tex4ht:ref: plot --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-376003"></a> for details on the <span class="cmbx-10">index (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-151000III"><span class="cmbx-10">103</span><!--tex4ht:ref: index --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-376004"></a>, <span class="cmbx-10">every</span>
<span class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-149000III"><span class="cmbx-10">101</span><!--tex4ht:ref: every --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-376005"></a>, and <span class="cmbx-10">using (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-164000III"><span class="cmbx-10">109</span><!--tex4ht:ref: using --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-376006"></a> directives. Data points are filtered against both xrange and yrange before
analysis. See <span class="cmbx-10">set xrange (p.</span><span class="cmbx-10">&nbsp;</span><a href="#x1-334000III"><span class="cmbx-10">218</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xrange --></a><span class="cmbx-10">)</span><a id="dx1-376007"></a>. The summary is printed to the screen by default. Output can be
redirected to a file by prior use of the command <span class="cmbx-10">set print</span>, or suppressed altogether using the <span class="cmbx-10">nooutput</span>
option.
<!--l. 15360--><p class="noindent">In addition to printed output, the program stores the individual statistics into three sets of variables. The first set of
variables reports how the data is laid out in the file: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;STATS_records</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;total</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;number</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;of</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;in-range</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;data</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;records</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;STATS_outofrange</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;number</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;of</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;records</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;filtered</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;out</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;by</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;range</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;limits</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;STATS_invalid</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;number</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;of</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;invalid/incomplete/missing</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;records</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;STATS_blank</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;number</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;of</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;blank</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;lines</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;in</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;the</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;file</span></span><span class="p">
</span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;STATS_blocks</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="C">#</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;number</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;of</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;indexable</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;data</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;blocks</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;in</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;the</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="C">&nbsp;file</span></span>
<!--l. 15370--></pre>
<!--l. 15373--><p class="noindent">The second set reports properties of the in-range data from a single column. If the corresponding axis is autoscaled
(x-axis for the 1st column, y-axis for the optional second column) then no range limits are applied. If two columns
