<!--l. 15811--><p class="noindent">The command-line syntax for these is, for example,
<!--l. 15813--></p><p class="noindent">Example: </p><pre><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;gnuplot</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;-background</span><span class="cmtt-10">&nbsp;coral</span>
<!--l. 15817--></pre>
<!--l. 15820--><p class="noindent">
</p><h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a id="x1-392000IV"></a>Grayscale_resources</h5>
<a id="Q1-1-779"></a>
<!--l. 15826--><p class="noindent">When <span class="cmbx-10">-gray </span>is selected, <span class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>honors the following resources for grayscale or color displays (shown here with
their default values). Note that the default background is black.
</p><div>
