</p><h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a id="x1-448000IV"></a>Pbm</h4>
<a id="Q1-1-891"></a>
<a id="dx1-448001"></a>
<!--l. 18859--><p class="noindent">Syntax: </p><pre class="prettyprint"><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="k">set</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;terminal</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;pbm</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="o">{&lt;</span><span class="p">fontsize</span><span class="o">&gt;}</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;{&lt;</span><span class="p">mode</span><span class="o">&gt;}</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="o">&nbsp;{</span><span class="p">size</span></span><span class="cmtt-10"><span class="p">&nbsp;</span><span class="s">&lt;x&gt;</span><span class="o">,&lt;</span><span class="p">y</span><span class="o">&gt;}</span></span>
<!--l. 18863--></pre>
<!--l. 18866--><p class="noindent">where <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>fontsize<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>is <span class="cmbx-10">small</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">medium</span>, or <span class="cmbx-10">large </span>and <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>mode<span class="cmmi-10">&gt; </span>is <span class="cmbx-10">monochrome</span>, <span class="cmbx-10">gray </span>or <span class="cmbx-10">color</span>. The default plot size
is 640 pixels wide and 480 pixels high. The output size is white-space padded to the nearest multiple of 8 pixels on
both x and y. This empty space may be cropped later if needed.
<!--l. 18871--></p><p class="noindent">The output of the <span class="cmbx-10">pbm </span>driver depends upon <span class="cmmi-10">&lt;</span>mode<span class="cmmi-10">&gt;</span>: <span class="cmbx-10">monochrome </span>produces a portable bitmap (one bit per
pixel), <span class="cmbx-10">gray </span>a portable graymap (three bits per pixel) and <span class="cmbx-10">color </span>a portable pixmap (color, four bits per
pixel).
<!--l. 18875--></p><p class="noindent">The output of this driver can be used with various image conversion and manipulation utilities provided by
NETPBM. Based on Jef Poskanzer's PBMPLUS package, NETPBM provides programs to convert the above PBM
formats to GIF, TIFF, MacPaint, Macintosh PICT, PCX, X11 bitmap and many others. Complete information is
available at http://netpbm.sourceforge.net/.
