<!--l. 21295--><p class="noindent">
</p><h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a id="x1-493000IV"></a>X11 other_resources</h5>
<a id="Q1-1-981"></a>
<a id="dx1-493001"></a>
<!--l. 21302--><p class="noindent">By default the contents of the current plot window are exported to the X11 clipboard in response to
X events in the window. Setting the resource 'gnuplot*exportselection' to 'off' or 'false' will disable
this.
<!--l. 21306--></p><p class="noindent">By default text rotation is done using a method that is fast, but can corrupt nearby colors depending on the
background. If this is a problem, you can set the resource 'gnuplot.fastrotate' to 'off'
</p><div>
<!--l. 21311--><p class="noindent">
</p><div class="tabular"> <table id="TBL-27" class="tabular" rules="groups" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><colgroup id="TBL-27-1g"><col id="TBL-27-1"><col id="TBL-27-2"></colgroup><tbody><tr class="hline"><td><hr></td><td><hr></td></tr><tr class="hline"><td><hr></td><td><hr></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align: baseline;" id="TBL-27-1-"><td style="white-space: nowrap; text-align: center;" id="TBL-27-1-1" class="td11"></td><td style="white-space: nowrap; text-align: left;" id="TBL-27-1-2" class="td11">gnuplot*exportselection: off</td>
</tr><tr style="vertical-align: baseline;" id="TBL-27-2-"><td style="white-space: nowrap; text-align: center;" id="TBL-27-2-1" class="td11"> </td><td style="white-space: nowrap; text-align: left;" id="TBL-27-2-2" class="td11">gnuplot*fastrotate: on       </td>
</tr><tr style="vertical-align: baseline;" id="TBL-27-3-"><td style="white-space: nowrap; text-align: center;" id="TBL-27-3-1" class="td11"> </td><td style="white-space: nowrap; text-align: left;" id="TBL-27-3-2" class="td11">gnuplot*ctrlq: off              </td>
